From: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Date: Thu, 28 Apr 2022 14:23:18 -0700
Subject: eth: benet: remove a copy of the NAPI_POLL_WEIGHT define
Patch-mainline: v5.19-rc1
Git-commit: e702def527ecdeabe0c8a302db0370161892d740
References: jsc#PED-1497

Defining local versions of NAPI_POLL_WEIGHT with the same
values in the drivers just makes refactoring harder.

Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be.h      |    3 +--
 drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be_main.c |    2 +-
 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be.h
@@ -101,8 +101,7 @@
 #define MAX_ROCE_EQS		5
 #define MAX_MSIX_VECTORS	32
 #define MIN_MSIX_VECTORS	1
-#define BE_NAPI_WEIGHT		64
-#define MAX_RX_POST		BE_NAPI_WEIGHT /* Frags posted at a time */
+#define MAX_RX_POST		NAPI_POLL_WEIGHT /* Frags posted at a time */
 #define RX_FRAGS_REFILL_WM	(RX_Q_LEN - MAX_RX_POST)
 #define MAX_NUM_POST_ERX_DB	255u
 
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be_main.c
@@ -2983,7 +2983,7 @@ static int be_evt_queues_create(struct b
 		cpumask_set_cpu(cpumask_local_spread(i, numa_node),
 				eqo->affinity_mask);
 		netif_napi_add(adapter->netdev, &eqo->napi, be_poll,
-			       BE_NAPI_WEIGHT);
+			       NAPI_POLL_WEIGHT);
 	}
 	return 0;
 }
